 As such, a total sample size of 600 eligible infants in Homa Bay, Kenya; 600 eligible infants in Rakai, Uganda; and 600 eligible infants in Iringa, Tanzania will be enrolled, assuming successful recruitment and follow-up of a total of 1500 (83%) patients, or 500 patients per country.

