10 using logistic regression to estimate adjusted odds ratios of moderate/severe AEs by arm.

 For outcomes with an incidence <10%, the modified Poisson regression will be used to estimate adjusted prevalence rate ratios.

 A formal interim analysis will be conducted after 200 circumcisions have been completed.

 Study accrual will be suspended for the interim analysis.

 The analysis will be for futility only.

 If after 200 infants have been enrolled and followed for 42 days it is found that the (non-inferiority) p-value is 0.

97 or greater (corresponding to a z-statistic of 1.

